<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1684" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1684">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/707.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 11.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 19, 1914.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department of State acknowledges the
                            receipt of your note of October 16, 1914, in which you state that the
                            Nicaraguan Government will not undertake to obtain from the Nicaraguan
                            Congress ratification of the proposed agreement with Messrs. Brown
                            Brothers &amp; Company and Seligman &amp; Company, postponing for four
                            months the payment of interest on the debt which the Government of
                            Nicaragua owes to these bankers.</p>
                        <p>The Department of State views with sympathy the efforts which the
                            Nicaraguan Government is making to arrange a difficult financial
                            situation and will be pleased to receive any further information that
                            you desire to place before it.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>